Transform your walks in just a few simple steps! 👇🏼

1. Ditch the retractable leash!!
2. Introduce a slip-lead (fitted properly) **This tool may not work for EVERY dog & that’s ok!** 
3. Teach your dog pressure & release 
4. Reward slack in the leash & engagement with YOU
5. Increase difficulty and HAVE FUN! 

#leashpulling #leashmanners #pulling #walks #dogwalks #looseleashwalking #dogtrainingtips

Let your dog think!!! 

Far too often we are stepping in to “save the day”. When in reality, we’re only making things worse. 

Stepping back & letting your dog calm their own mind is one of the best things you can do for your dog. You’ll notice a difference almost immediately!! 

#separationanxiety #anxiety #anxiousdog #fomo #tantrum #dogtraining

Uncomfortable situations can produce incredible outcomes!!! 

How can we expect our dogs to learn & grow if we never give them a little push? 

No, I’m not saying ignore your dog’s threshold and push them to the point of shutting down. 

But I am saying that a little pressure is HEALTHY and can transform the way your dog perceives the world. 

What are some ways you help your dog work through somewhat stressful situations?? 👇🏼

#dogtrainer #dogtrainingtips #stresseddog #growth

If you let your dog pull, your dog will KEEP pulling!!! 

This is a simple step to see quick results, but you MUST stay consistent. 

Start where there are no distractions. Anytime the leash gets tight, turn around. Mark with “yes!” as soon as your dog follows you. Continue to do this until your dog begins to OFFER the good behavior. Bring out your dogs favorite treats and watch how quickly your walk is transformed! 

#dogtrainer #dogtraining #leashmanners #leashwalking #balancedtraining

Not only is this a super common issue, it’s also VERY dangerous! 😬

You should be able to grab a package off your porch or calmly let guests in without having to quickly catch & pull your dog back. 

If you commit 5-10min per day working on this exercise, you’ll see a totally different (and safer!) dog in no time. 

Don’t forget to stay consistent!!!
What you don’t use, you’ll lose. That goes for your dog too ;) 

#trainingtips #dogtraining #doorbolting #doormanners #thresholdmanners

It’s easy to get frustrated when it feels like your dog is ignoring you. 
Well, that’s because you’ve taught your dog it’s OK to ignore you!!! 🫣

Instead, teach your dog that your commands hold VALUE.  Let your dog solve the problem ON THEIR OWN without you feeling the need to repeat your words over, and over and over.

Your dog will learn that your command holds MEANING and that the reward only ever comes if they listen the first time. 

Remember, you only have to say it ONCE! 😉

#dogtrainingtips #dogtrainer #sayitonce

Sure, dog parks sound great in theory.. But actually, they can cause far more harm than good. 

They are unregulated, meaning any dog (healthy or not, friendly or not) can come in. 
They can lead to injury & behavioral issues - even if your dog is not the “problem”. 
They can teach your dog that when they see other dogs, they’re allowed to go CRAZY! 

There are so many other ways to properly socialize and physically wear out your dog, such as: 
•Agility - This one will not only tire your dog out, but can also work towards confidence building. 
•Pack walks with friends! Rather than setting up a “puppy play date,” a puppy pack walk is much more productive! You can target leash training and socialization all in one! 
 •Training outside the dog park - You can still use the dog park to your advantage by allowing your dog to observe the other dogs, practicing commands with distractions, and more! 
 •Mentally stimulating activities like snuffle mats, healthy chews, & brain games. 

What are some ways you properly socialize & exercise your dog? 

#dogparks #nomoredogparks #socialization #dogtraining #dogpark #advocate

#dogtraining #goldenretriever #crazy #jumping #leashpulling #tomford

Jumping is cute… Until it isn’t!! 

1. It’s so easy to allow the jumping for one, maybe two minutes when you first get home. But I’m sure after a couple minutes you find yourself scolding your dog because “that’s enough!” Well, your dog doesn’t understand. You were just encouraging the jumping a second ago? It’s only fair to be consistent with your expectations. Your dog will quickly catch on! 

2. Disagree with the jumping by using a leash. Dogs are opportunists. If the opportunity isn’t even a possibility, it can’t happen! 

3. Teach your dog what you DO want. Your dog wants your attention. Teach them how to properly earn it!! 

Bonus: Teach your puppy early!!! What’s cute now will not be cute later 😉

#dogtraining #stopjumping #nomorejumping #dogtrainingtips

Yes, this video is based on (mostly) real-life instances 😂

- You only need to bring your dog’s food & leash. Healthy treats are welcomed. You don’t need a whole suitcase of toys or blankies 😉

#dogmom #dogdad #funny #dogmoms #dogdads

‼️ Never chase your dog ‼️
This is only teaching your dog that it’s FUN to run away from you. There’s no circumstance where that should be ok!! 
Instead, teach your dog to WANT to follow you & watch how quickly your recall improves! 

#dogtraining #dogtrainingtips #dogtrainer #recall #balancedtraining

Do THIS to save your dog’s life!! 

There is nothing more scary (and dangerous!) than your dog bolting out the door & into the street. Just like there is nothing more annoying than having to body-block your dog while you let guests in / simply grab a package off the porch. 🥴

Teach your dog that an open door means NOTHING.

YOU are the only one that gives the “ok” for them to exit/enter the door. This goes for the crate, the front door, back door AND car doors! 

Also keep in mind that it matters WHEN you release your dog. Are they looking to YOU for the release or are they eagerly staring out the door ready to bolt? 👀

Not only is this safe for your dog; but this impulse control will translate to many other forms of obedience!! 

Does YOUR dog understand threshold manners?? 🐶

#dogtraining #trainingtip #dogtrainer #safetyfirst

INTRO TO PLACE - Part 1 

The place command is one of my FAVORITES! It serves so many purposes. Teaching a stay, providing a job, encouraging a calm mindset - just to name a few! 

If you’re ready to teach your dog “place”, here are the first few steps! 👇🏼

1) Put your dog on a leash or long-line 
2) Grab some treats - try to use your dog’s kibble! 
3) Use your body language to encourage movement onto the bed. Avoid using verbal commands. 
4) All 4 paws on bed = reward! 
5) Practice from multiple angles 
6) Walk around to introduce an implied stay 
7) Use the leash to disagree with unwanted behavior 
8) Don’t reward bare minimum effort! 
BONUS: The crouch test!! 

If you have questions about introducing place, ask away in the comments! 👇🏼

#dogtraining #dogtrainer #place #stay #gsp #training #balancedtraining

3 tips to CHANGE the way you walk your dog! 

1) If your first goal is a long walk, odds are that long walk is probably not going to be a fun one. You need to first teach your dog HOW to walk with you before expecting to have an enjoyable walk. Start small!! You might look crazy making circles in your driveway, but hey, look crazy & watch the progress! 

2) Turn around. If pulling works, your dog is going to keep pulling!! Instead, teach your dog to FOLLOW instead of pull. 

3) The drop-back. This is an AMAZING way to build engagement between you & your dog. You must be more exciting than anything else!! You’ll quickly notice your dog WANTING to stay near you. 

Let me know once you’ve tried all 3 steps & how it worked for you!! Remember, stay consistent! 

#leashpulling #leashmanners #dogtraining #dogtrainer

Let your dog think!!!

I’ve had so many people ask me how I fixed Bluebell’s tantrums in the crate.

Truth is, I didn’t do much. In fact, I just let. her. be. Although that may sound simple, a LOT of people struggle to just “let their dog be”. 

By allowing Bluebell to learn to settle her OWN mind, she learned very quickly that barking & screaming in my face was going to get her nowhere. I paid it no attention. 

Within 15 minutes; she was lying down. Calmly breathing. Just chillin’. 

Within an hour, she was lying down in the kennel with the door wide open while I stood 10ft away. 

There is SO much power in letting your dog think. Avoid stepping in unless you have to. And watch what happens!!

Leave a comment if you’d like a more detailed, step by step video on this process! 

#fomo #gsp #cratetraining #crate #tantrum #dogtraining

Did you know that dogs CRAVE structure?? 

Your dog shredding your shoe, biting your furniture or leaving scratches from excessive jumping/nipping is your dog showing you they need YOUR guidance. 

Your dog doesn’t understand that pottying in the house is “naughty”. Or that jumping on your grandma is “rude”. It’s our job as owners to lead our dogs. To lead them with CLARITY. 

Within one session, Ranger was looking like a different dog. Because we were clear in our expectations and consistent with the follow-through. 

What are some unwanted behaviors your dog does? How are some ways you can communicate & lead them better? 

#trainingtips #boundaries #redbonecoonhound #dogtraining #clarity #guidance #structure #transformation

Bombarding guests at the door is one of the BIGGEST issues I see requested from owners. 
Well, here’s one way you can begin to transform the way your dog greets guests!

Introduce the place command. 

This gives your dog a JOB. A job that is not rushing up to the door, barking, jumping, scratching, etc!

1. Introduce the place bed WITHOUT distractions first. (Check out our “how to intro the place command” reel!) 
2. Build up duration and distractions slowly. Keep a leash on your dog for communication!! 
3. Add in a knock on the door. I suggest having someone else to hold the leash or using a tether + anchor. Do not act excited!!! It shouldn’t be a big deal. If your dog gets up, use the leash to bring them back to the bed. 
4. Each time your dog chooses to remain on the bed while there’s a knock or ring on the doorbell, praise praise praise!!
5. When you do have guests come over, ASK THEM TO IGNORE YOUR DOG as they walk in. This part is SO important!! 
6. Teach your dog a release word to come off the bed. Make sure you’re not releasing your dog until they have a calm, settled mindset!! 
7. Ask your guests to only give your dog attention if “all 4 are on the floor”. No jumping!
8. Keep your dog guessing by changing up the way/routine in which you train!
9. Raise expectations and add different distractions daily!! 

Now it’s your turn!
Let me know some other issues you’re having with your dog, I’d love to help! 

#dogtraining #place #transformation #dogtrainingtips

PSA: Crate trained = CALM mindset in the crate. Not just “my dog tolerates the crate”. 

This can be accomplished many different ways, this is just one way!! 

Make sure you don’t rescue your dog when they get frustrated. Let them work it out!! It’s ok to let them be a little bit stressed out. They need to be able to solve the problem on their own. 

TIP: Be patient. Don’t plan to work on this if you do not have time. A lot of my time during this video was spent waiting. Waiting to CAPTURE that settled, calm mindset. 

Let me know how this goes with your dog!! 

#cratetrain #cratetraining #husky #dogtraining

We all know the struggle of trying to work with a dog whose attention is ANYWHERE but on us. Smells, squirrels, people, other dogs, the list goes on and on.

In this video we are incorporating the place bed as a way to teach & reinforce a calm mindset, which in turn; lowers frustration, minimizes confusion and provides reliable results no matter what you’re working through! 

With a calm mind comes CLEAR communication. 

During this session I tethered Sully to a leash anchor so he could not just hop off the bed whenever he felt like it. Then I let him hang out on the bed with no additional command as long as all four paws remained on the bed. I wanted him to decide on his OWN how to relax and calm his mind. I wanted him to “solve the problem” independently. 

He stayed standing & fidgeting for a while. After a while he realized this wasn’t getting anywhere so he decided to sit. After several minutes he VOLUNTARILY went into a down position. He let out a big sigh of relief and he breathing immediately slowed. Why wouldn’t we want this for our dogs? 

Does your dog know how to settle? It all starts with YOU! Now it’s your turn, happy training! 🫶🏻

#calmmindset #settle #dogtraining

Move = To create space! 

This command can be used in so many different situations. To name a few, 
1) When your dog wants to be right under your feet while you’re cooking 
2) When your dog is bothering your other dog / invading their personal space 
3) When your dog is too close to the door as you’re trying to open it 

And many more! 
Don’t hear me wrong, this command is not meant to REPLACE obedience commands. It’s just to provide a momentary solution to a sticky situation. Plus, it’s fun to teach! 

What are some ways you can use “move” with your dog?

#dogtraining #dogtrainer #personalspace

“Training tools are CRUEL!” 

My first response is always, “Have you actually used them?”

Most people who claim that tools are abusive, are people who have never actually put hands on them. Never actually studied WHY a prong collar works so beautifully & is SO safe for a dog’s neck. Never even felt a (real) E-collar on their own skin. 

Because once you have, there’s no way you can call these tools abusive. 
 Sure, ANY tool can be used improperly. A LEASH can be used poorly. FOOD can be used poorly. ATTENTION can be used poorly. But it’s naive to put a label on something you don’t actually have any experience with. 

I have seen SO many dogs earn SO much more freedom (and FUN!) because of training tools. And no, that doesn’t make me a lazy trainer or the owner a lazy owner. It just means we’re seeing the VALUE a properly conditioned training tool can provide. 

Drop a comment if YOU use training tools! 👇🏼

#ecollar #prongcollar #trainingtools #balancedtraining #dogtraining

3 ways to make mealtime FUN, without spending a dime!! 

1) Sprinkle the food into the grass. This provides a fun hunting game for your dog! 
2) Roll their food into a towel, wet it, and freeze! This creates a fun popsicle / puzzle toy. Talk about mental stimulation!
3) Use meal time as training time!! Food is a primary resource to your dog. Make it fun!!! (And save LOTS of money on treats!) 

How else do you make your dog’s mealtime a fun time? 

#dogtraining #mentalstimulation #dogtrainer #braingames

“PLACE” - Part 2!!

The place command is useful for SO many different things. 

That’s why we TRAIN to PREPARE for the real life instances!!! 

Here are 4 ways to proof your dog’s place-stay!!

1. Vacuum!! A lot of dogs I work with either want to chase the vacuum, or are terrified of the vacuum. Either way, incorporating the place command while you vacuum is an incredible way to resolve both of these issues. 
2. Open the door, knock on the door, go out of sight! This one will most likely be SUPER tough for your dog at first, so be patient!!! 
3. Cook/clean!!! Often times we get frustrated with our dogs for being right up under our feet while we’re in the kitchen. So why not solve that problem with place?
4. Relax/hang out on the couch/watch TV! Sure, there’s always time for cuddle time, but why not throw some “brain work” in for your dog? The place command is mentally exhausting for your dog - so use it!!! 

What are some ways you use place with your dog?? 

#dogtraining #placecommand #stay #gsp

Why are we hating and banning tools that can give dogs a better, safer, more fulfilled life? 

Oh, right. Because we don’t truly know anything about them. 

If you don’t want to use training tools with your dog, that’s your choice! But it’s not your place to bully someone else for having a different opinion/experience/choice. 

For myself, I can say, I am proud to be able to use my “toolbox” to better my dog’s life! 

#trainingtools #balancedtrainer #dogtrainer #ecollar #prongcollar #crate

E-COLLARS ARE NOT SHOCK COLLARS!!

True E-Collars (we use @ecollartechnologies) use static stimulation like a tens unit or muscle stimulator. When used properly, we are able to successfully (and figuratively) whisper, talk or shout to our dogs depending on the level of stimulation. 
Use it properly, and your dog will LOVE their E-collar. 

I will ALWAYS have the owner feel the E-collar on their palm before ever putting it on their dog. Almost always, their reaction is the same; “Wait. That’s what it feels like?? That’s it??” 

Yep. That’s it. And your dog’s baseline level is typically LOWER than that!

When using E-collars, we are looking for a RESPONSE, not a REACTION. 

E-Collars are designed to provide reliable COMMUNICATION when used properly. Not inflict pain. 

What number do you feel on the E-collar VS what level does your dog work on? Personally, I feel it on an 18 and my dog works on a 3!! 👇🏼

#ecollar #ecollartraining #dogtraining #dogtrainer

POV: Your dog is a goofy, friendly pup.. But they act super vicious towards other dogs when on the leash. What’s going on?

First thing I’m looking for.. How are YOU communicating with your dog? 

Are you tensing up as soon as you see another dog? Are you panicking to find a different route to avoid the other dog? Are you immediately trying to comfort your dog with petting and sweet-talking? 

It all starts with us. Our mindset. What our body language is telling our dog. Then, we move onto the dog. What is their mindset showing us? Are they frustrated? Scared? Overly excited? 

Don’t forget to check in with yourself before going on a walk. What are you expectations for this walk? What are your goals? And if you need help figuring those out, we’re here to help! 

What do walks with your dog look like? Let us know in the comments! 

#reactivedog #bts #pov #dogtrainer #dogtraining

PSA: Just because YOU want to pet a dog… Does not mean you should. Especially if the dog’s owner/trainer has kindly asked you not to. 

Not only is ignoring this request inconsiderate, it’s also a safety risk. That dog may not WANT to be pet. If you didn’t like hugs, would you want any and everyone huggin’ all over you? 

It’s also really discouraging for an owner to work so diligently to teach their dog to not jump on guests just for you to say “Ah, it’s OK I don’t mind!” 
Well, the owner DOES mind. 

Do them (and yourself) a favor, and respect their request! It’s really not that hard. ❤️

#dogtraining #dogtrainer #respectboundaries

“Good thing he’s tiny or that would be bad!!!”

Actually.. It’s still bad. And your tiny dog deserves better!!

Just because you can easily pick up your dog when they’re barking, nipping, chasing, etc. doesn’t mean it should stay that way. 

Why not teach your pup what to do instead? Why not hold them to a higher standard?

In fact, your dog acting poorly is them SHOWING you how much they NEED you to expect more from them!! 

Remember, little dogs are still dogs. And our dogs deserve better. 

Leave a comment if YOU have a little dog!! 👇🏼

#littledog #tinydog #trainyourdog #dogtrainer

A reliable recall is one of the MOST important things you can teach your dog - especially for safety!!! 
Here are 3 tips to help improve and strengthen your dog’s recall!
1. Don’t just take the leash off and hope for the best! We recommend using a 15-30ft long-line (linked on our website) to make it “seem” as if there’s no leash, but to still have as back-up. Practice just letting your dog check in with you! Mark with “yes!” and occasionally give a reward. Bonus if you use their kibble! 
2. Make sure you’re using the same word every time! We often get into a bad habit of just throwing around random, casual phrases instead of a specific cue/word. Remember, dogs don’t speak English! 
3. Play fun recall games!! This teaches your dog it is FUN to come when called! Puppy Ping Pong and Hide n’ Seek are two of our favs. You can start these as soon as you bring your pup home!

Which tip is your favorite?? 

#recall #dogtraining #dogtrainer #traininggames

Did you see yourself in this video? 👀

Dog moms are 100% some of the most entertaining to people watch 😂 

All jokes aside, a happy “middle ground” of safe AND fun is the way to go!! 

#dogmoms #dogmom #furbaby #funny

No, you don’t need to put your hand in their face!! 
This is the perfect way to ask for a dog bite. 

Trust me, the dog can smell you just fine without your hand being forced up into their face. 

Instead, let the dog learn to trust you. Don’t force yourself on the dog just because “dogs love you”. 

Warning signs to look for from a nervous dog: 
- Backing away 
- Stiff body language 
- Head tucked 
- Wide eyes 
- Trembling 

Let’s educate others & advocate to respect dogs’ space!! 

#dogtrainer #advocate #nervousdog #nopet

Help your dog work THROUGH tough situations instead of always running to the “rescue”. 

Structure leads to a calm, safe & happy pup. 

If I didn’t disagree with the tantrum in the crate, Suki could’ve really hurt herself. Plus, why would I want a dog to stay in such a stressed state of mind? 

Instead, we worked through the situation and I taught her what I wanted instead. Which in turn, led to a calm, relaxed mindset  and SAFE end result. 

So which dog is happier? The one who had no rules, or the one who now has structure? 

#separationanxiety #fomo #demandbarking #dogtraining

Build confidence & burn excess energy, all in one! 

The treadmill is one of my favorite things to implement, especially on rainy days. 
Not only does it provide a great way for your dog to burn off some energy, but it’s an incredible way to help nervous/insecure dogs build up their confidence. 

Of course, anything can be used TOO much so make sure you take into account what your dog can handle. 
For example, my german shepherd is going to run quite a bit longer/faster than the little pup in this video. 

I hope you found this helpful!! Let me know in the comments if you do - or are going to - use the treadmill with YOUR dog! 

#confidencebuilding #treadmill #dogtraining #dogtreadmill

Too often, we get frustrated with our dogs for crazy, out of control behaviors, when WE are the ones to encourage these behaviors in the first place. 

Instead of creating chaos, YOU need to be setting the example of what a calm mindset should look like. 

Someone comes your door? Act normal! It’s no big deal. Your dog will follow your lead. 
Time for a walk? Again, act casual! It doesn’t need to be a whole fiasco. Wait for a calm, relaxed mindset before even opening the door. 
Arrive somewhere new? Hold your dog accountable to a down-stay and on YOUR release, allow them to calmly exit the car.

Your dog craves structure! It’s our job to give it to them. 

#mistakes #dogowner #dogtrainer #dogtraining

Do you actually know what your dog is thinking? 

It’s important to take into consideration that our dogs are dogs. Not people. They interpret / understand the world WAY differently than we do. 

1) Affection - most dogs do not enjoy excessive hugs/squeezes/pets. This can be extremely overwhelming for your dog and can sometimes lead to a bite if you don’t listen to their warning signs! 
2) Your words/commands - your dog doesn’t speak english!! It’s important to limit how many words you throw at your dog, they only understand the ones you teach them! 
3) Dramatic goodbyes - I know, we all do this at some point. But more than likely, your dog is totally fine when you leave. (And if your dog is anxious when you leave, it’s because you may have created an anxious dog with your dramatic, drawn-out goodbyes.)

PSA: The dog park does not provide proper socialization for your dog. ⚠️

What is does provide:
• Unregulated dogs with rude/obnoxious/dangerous behaviors 
• Dog fights/injuries 
• Sickness/Diseases 
• Chaos! 

There are SO many other ways to properly socialize your dog without risking any of the above: 

•Pack walks with friends! Rather than setting up a “puppy play date,” a puppy pack walk is much more productive! You can target leash training and socialization all in one! 
• Calmly hangin’ out with other well-behaved dogs at a park or restaurant patio! 
•Agility - This one will not only tire your dog out, but can also work towards confidence building. 
 •Training outside the dog park - You can still use the dog park to your advantage by allowing your dog to observe the other dogs, practicing commands with distractions, and more! 
 •Mentally stimulating activities like snuffle mats, healthy chews, & brain games.

BE A RESPONSIBLE DOG OWNER!!!

This is SO dangerous on so many levels! 

I understand that this owner had no poor intentions but this scenario could’ve played out FAR differently if I had been working with one of my reactive or fearful pups. FAR different.. And it’s not fair!

Please, respect others and keep your dog under control at all times! It’s safer for everyone.

Small changes go a LONG way!! 

By just incorporating 5 simple steps, Heidi was looking like a new pup in just a matter of 20 minutes. 

Here are the five steps to creating a calmer greeting when guests arrive: 

1) Leash your dog! Crazy how much can be managed with a simple leash. In this video we are also using the @hermsprengerusa prong collar to better communicate with Heidi. 
2) Use your body to create space! We communicate with our dogs SO much with our bodies, so make sure you’re being consistent! By turning INTO your dog, they will naturally back up! 
3) Use the leash to disagree with the jumping & pair with a word like “off”. Remember to reward when your dog chooses to keep all four paws on the floor!
4) Practice several repetitions & use different people! 
5) Reinforce good choices!! You’ll notice your dog begin to offer the correct behavior, reward these moments!!

‼️Controversial opinion‼️

Puppies do not make the best Christmas present.. Here’s why. 

Timing plays a huge role. The holiday season is a crazy, busy season. Not only can this time be VERY overwhelming for a new puppy, the craziness doesn’t allow you much time to dedicate to raising your puppy once they’re home. Puppies have a critical socialization window and the holiday season makes it very difficult to dedicate necessary time & energy into fulfilling the puppy’s needs. 

Most puppies are not going to be the “perfect age” and ready to be gifted on Christmas morning. Therefore, you’re either getting a puppy who’s way too young, or one who’s been “held back” and has missed out on a super important socialization window. 

Choosing a puppy requires a LOT of research. Does this breed fit this person’s lifestyle? Do I adopt? Do I shop? Can I trust this breeder? Will this dog need grooming? Will this dog need training? (YES!), Can they afford what this dog needs? How will they be fulfilled? How will they get exercise? The list goes on! This is a BIG decision to make for someone else or have someone else make for you. Unfortunately, so many puppies often end up in shelters due to a lack of preparation and/or lifestyle. 

If you are getting a puppy for Christmas, make sure to do your research. Make sure this puppy is a good fit for the family and their lifestyle. Make sure that this puppy can be financially supported and given the time, effort & dedication it deserves. 

A puppy is not just a cute Christmas present. 
A puppy is a lifetime commitment. 

#controversial #unpopularopinion #shopresponsibly #blackfriday #dogsareforlife #commitment
